  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime and has demonstrated remorse by making partial restitution. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, a 10-year sentence suggested by the spectator is disproportionate to the amount embezzled ($25,000) and the defendant's lack of prior criminal history. Considering standard sentencing guidelines for a first offense of this nature, a period of 6 months of incarceration is appropriate to reflect the severity of the breach of professional duty while allowing for rehabilitation and future restitution.",
  "verdict": 6
